Governor Samuel Ortom has cleared the air on his rumoured senatorial ambition as he formally sought the blessings of his kinsmen to contest the Benue Northwest Senatorial seat. The governor at a meeting with his Nzorov kinsmen comprising traditional rulers and other leaders on Saturday, March 5th, 2022 told them that he was now convinced to contest the Zone B Senate seat on the platform of the People’s Democratic Party, PDP. The District Head of Nzorov, Chief Gwatse Akaahena, who spoke on behalf of traditional and political leaders gave their nod and affirmed their support for the governor to go ahead and run for the senate seat. The traditional ruler said they were in full support of their son to not only contest and win the senate seat but also conquer higher offices. On Monday, July 16, 2018, Benue state governor, Samuel Ortom, announced that he had been issued a red card by the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the state. In contemplation of the governor’s claim, three realities readily come to mind. The first reality is that he had never been in… In "Politics" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Mr. Nathaniel Ikyur, the Chief Press Secretary (CPS), to Benue State Governor, Dr. Samuel Ortom, has declared that his principal does not hate President Muhammad Buhari. According to Ikyur, Ortom's statements on the state of the nation should not be misconstrued for demeaning… In "Politics" Makurdi- Senate President David Mark, Gov. Gabriel Suswam and Mike Mku on Saturday picked the PDP's ticket to contest the 2015 general elections in their respective senatorial zones in Benue. A correspondent of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) who covered the primaries for Benue South Senatorial District, reported that… In "News"